Weather and Boats

Ernesto Carrella

September 8, 2015

Mini-demo here, just to show the current implementation of weather and how it affects fishers. By default weather is constant and boats ignore it altogether, but in this simulation I add a perfectly oscillating wind-speed that goes from 0 to 100 km/h. Boats have their own threshold of maximum windspeed \(\sim N(50,10)\).
If windspeed goes above their threshold, they go home and don’t leave until the weather gets better.
